## Using This System in Cursor

All shared instructions, working rules, and source-of-truth hierarchy are
loaded above from \`.github/copilot-instructions.md\`.

### Prompt Files

The project lifecycle prompts live in \`.github/prompts/\`. Open them directly
or reference their content in chat:

| Prompt file | What it does |
|---|---|
| \`.github/prompts/project.prompt.md\` | Start or resume a project (full lifecycle) |
| \`.github/prompts/begin-project.prompt.md\` | Alias for project |
| \`.github/prompts/save.prompt.md\` | Save session progress |
| \`.github/prompts/end.prompt.md\` | End session with commit message |
| \`.github/prompts/review.prompt.md\` | Code review against project standards |

### Agent Files

Specialist agents are defined in \`.github/agents/\`. Reference them when
their domain fits the task:
- \`@project-manager\` — lifecycle orchestration
- \`@contract-agent\` — scope definition one question at a time
- \`@senior-engineer\` — production implementation
- \`@test-agent\` — test creation and review
- \`@design-agent\` — UI/UX specs before implementation
- \`@docs-agent\` — developer-facing documentation
- \`@api-agent\` — backend/API endpoint work

### Skills

Skills live in \`.github/skills/\`. Reference by name:
- \`implementation-pipeline\` — end-to-end workflow for scoped changes

